hh3cMinm.name: hh3cMinm

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB.

hh3cMinm.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085

Hh3cMinmEnabledStatus.name: Hh3cMinmEnabledStatus
Hh3cMinmEnabledStatus.description: A enumerated value which indicates the state of object.

hh3cMinmCapabilities.name: hh3cMinmCapabilities
hh3cMinmCapabilities.description: This object displays the MAC-in-MAC capabilities with respect to certain fields. The following values may be supported: reEncapsulation: Support for configuring re-encapsulation (denoted by hh3cMinmVsiReEncapsulation). uplink: Support for configuring uplink (denoted by hh3cMinmUplinkTable). vsiShareConnection: It indicates that connection entry is shared in all VSIs. hh3cVsiIndex is meaningless and must be value 1 in hh3cMinmConnectionTable.

hh3cMinmBmac.name: hh3cMinmBmac
hh3cMinmBmac.description: A MAC address used in creating the MAC header of I-tagged frames transmitted across a Provider Backbone Bridged Network. The invalid value FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF indicates that this node is not supported by the device.

hh3cMinmVsiTable.name: hh3cMinmVsiTable
hh3cMinmVsiTable.description: A table for configuring MAC-in-MAC service instance parameter.

hh3cMinmVsiEntry.name: hh3cMinmVsiEntry
hh3cMinmVsiEntry.description: An entry for configuring MAC-in-MAC service instance parameter.

hh3cMinmVsiBvlan.name: hh3cMinmVsiBvlan
hh3cMinmVsiBvlan.description: BVLAN ID. The value 65535 indicates the BVLAN has not been configured for get operation, and it indicates deleting the BVLAN configration for set operation.

hh3cMinmVsiReEncapsulation.name: hh3cMinmVsiReEncapsulation
hh3cMinmVsiReEncapsulation.description: Whether the re-encapsulation is enabled. The reEncapsulation field of hh3cMinmCapabilities denotes whether this node is supported.

hh3cMinmVsiNextAvailableLinkId.name: hh3cMinmVsiNextAvailableLinkId
hh3cMinmVsiNextAvailableLinkId.description: Next available connection entry index for creating a connection entry. Its value ranges from 0x1 to 0xFFFFFFFF.The invalid value 0xFFFFFFFF indicates that connection entry can not be created. When the vsiShareConnection field of hh3cMinmCapabilities is set, this node returns an invalid value if the value of hh3cVsiIndex is not 1.

hh3cMinmUplinkTable.name: hh3cMinmUplinkTable
hh3cMinmUplinkTable.description: A table for uplink ports of the VSI in MAC-in-MAC. The uplink field of hh3cMinmCapabilities denotes whether this table is supported.

hh3cMinmUplinkEntry.name: hh3cMinmUplinkEntry
hh3cMinmUplinkEntry.description: An entry for uplink ports of the VSI in MAC-in-MAC.

hh3cMinmUplinkRowStatus.name: hh3cMinmUplinkRowStatus
hh3cMinmUplinkRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hh3cMinmConnectionTable.name: hh3cMinmConnectionTable
hh3cMinmConnectionTable.description: A table for the connection information of BMAC.

hh3cMinmConnectionEntry.name: hh3cMinmConnectionEntry
hh3cMinmConnectionEntry.description: An entry for the connection information of BMAC. When the vsiShareConnection field of hh3cMinmCapabilities is set, connection entry is shared in all VSIs. hh3cVsiIndex is meaningless and must be value 1 in hh3cMinmConnectionTable.

hh3cMinmConnectionLinkId.name: hh3cMinmConnectionLinkId
hh3cMinmConnectionLinkId.description: Entry index when the vsiShareConnection bit of hh3cMinmCapabilities is set(hh3cVsiIndex is meaningless and must be value 1), else entry index in the VSI of hh3cVsiIndex.Its value ranges from 0x1 to 0xFFFFFFFE. It should be obtained from hh3cMinmVsiNextAvailableLinkId for create operation.

hh3cMinmConnectionPort.name: hh3cMinmConnectionPort
hh3cMinmConnectionPort.description: Port ifindex of an connection entry.

hh3cMinmConnectionAgingStatus.name: hh3cMinmConnectionAgingStatus
hh3cMinmConnectionAgingStatus.description: Aging time of an connection entry.

hh3cMinmConnectionRowStatus.name: hh3cMinmConnectionRowStatus
hh3cMinmConnectionRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.
